    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Cooling System, and
        Related Components - Removal - Oil Pump Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Oil Pump Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f3350012297" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk13/k13015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front oil seal removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump and rotor housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front oil seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Be careful not to damage the crankshaft or front oil seal mounting surface while removing the
                    front oil seal.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1213" count="1">Remove the front oil seal with a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_299.xml" xrefid="t335001203">heel bar</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001203"/>
                or seal puller, while the oil pump and rotor housing assembly is attached to the front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard front oil seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350012298" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk13/k13011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump and rotor housing assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 60 bolt (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 25 bolt (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M8 x 60 bolts holding the oil pump and rotor housing to the front cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four M8 x 25 bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350012299" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk13/k13012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil pump housing and rotor assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump and rotor housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inner rotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer rotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump (housing) seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the oil pump and rotor housing and discard oil pump (housing) seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, use permanent marker to identify internal engine components and their
                    orientation. Do not use paint or temporary markers.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark inner and outer rotors with a permanent marker, if oil pump is to be reused. Mark will
                indicate rotor turning direction and orientation to front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove outer rotor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350012300" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK13/K13013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Vibration damper key, inner rotor, and oil pump housing plate</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration damper key</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Washer seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inner rotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil pump housing plate</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not damage or distort the crankshaft keyway groove during vibration
                    damper key removal.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully tap the vibration damper key out of the crankshaft with a hammer and chisel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove washer seal and inner rotor from crankshaft.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil pump housing plate.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil pump housing seal from front cover and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To remove the oil pump spline drive. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3351_403.xml" xrefid="s1606">Oil Pump Spline Drive</hotlnk>
                    removal
                    <xref refid="s1606"/>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
